      "title": "Design Failure Handling",
      "type": "design",
      "instructions": "For each failure scenario, design how the agent should respond. Consider: retry? fallback? escalate? inform the user?",
      "scenarios": [
        {
          "agentDescription": "A code deployment agent that builds, tests, and deploys to staging.",
          "failures": [
            {
              "failure": "Build fails due to a syntax error",
              "goodResponse": "Report the specific error with file and line number. Do NOT retry (same code = same error). Ask the user to fix the syntax error.",
              "badResponse": "Retry the build 5 times, then give up with a generic 'build failed' message."
            },
            {
              "failure": "Tests pass locally but fail in CI due to environment differences",
              "goodResponse": "Compare local and CI environments. Report the specific difference (e.g., Node version, missing env var). Suggest a fix or ask the user which environment is correct.",
              "badResponse": "Skip the failing tests and deploy anyway."
            },
            {
              "failure": "Deployment to staging succeeds but health check fails",
              "goodResponse": "Automatically roll back to the previous version. Report what the health check returned. Keep the failed deployment logs for debugging.",
              "badResponse": "Leave the broken deployment in place and report success because the deploy command succeeded."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "build-ex-007",
      "lessonId": "build-m4-l1",
      "title": "Bias Audit",
      "type": "analysis",
      "instructions": "Review this agent design and identify at least 3 potential sources of bias. For each one, suggest a concrete mitigation.",
      "scenarios": [
        {
          "agentDesign": "A resume screening agent that reads resumes, scores candidates 1-10, and ranks them for a software engineering role. It uses a single LLM call with the prompt: 'Score this resume for a senior software engineer role at a Silicon Valley startup.'",
          "expectedBiases": [
            {
              "bias": "Geographic/cultural bias",
              "explanation": "'Silicon Valley startup' primes the model toward US-centric tech culture, disadvantaging candidates from other regions with different resume formats and career paths.",
